description.narrative: New Element, which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 2. By 2021, children and adolescents at greater disadvantage, mainly those affected by violence, forced displacement and migration, have access to safe, inclusive, flexible and innovative forms of quality education.

title.narrative: New Element

description.narrative: In 2021, 48,350children and adolescents accessed the educational system through alternative and flexible modalities that allowed for continuity of learning in the most vulnerable regions of Honduras. Of these, 39,163 were reached through the humanitarian response to COVID-19, hurricanes Eta and Iota, and the situation of migrants, those who were displaced by violence and those in danger of dropping out of school.A total of 182,100children and adolescents received educational materials that allowed them to continue their studies, including among the most vulnerable populations, including the Miskito and Garifuna indigenous peoples. | Status:Met | As-of Date:27/01/2022
